      <p style="line-height: 100%; text-indent: 0px; word-spacing: 0px; margin: 0px" align="left"><b><font color="#AEC3DB" face="Tahoma" size="3">West
      Cabilis Quest Guide</font></b></p>
      <p style="line-height: 100%; text-indent: 0px; word-spacing: 0px; margin: 0px" align="left">&nbsp;</p>
      <p style="line-height: 100%; text-indent: 0px; word-spacing: 0px; margin: 0px" align="left">&nbsp;</p>
      <p style="line-height: 100%; text-indent: 0px; word-spacing: 0px; margin: 0px" align="left"><img border="0" src="../newsbar.gif" width="414" height="21"></p>
      <p style="line-height: 100%; text-indent: 0px; word-spacing: 0px; margin: 0px" align="left">&nbsp;</p>
      <p style="line-height: 100%; text-indent: 0px; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0" align="left">&nbsp;</p>
      <div>
        <font size="2">
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma" color="#FFFFFF">This
        is an initial attempt to map out the quests at West Cabilis.&nbsp; Feel
        free to send me an email with corrections, updates or additional
        information :)</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <b>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font face="Tahoma" color="#AEC3DB">Keeper
        Bile</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Tahoma"><font color="#FFFFFF">Julak</font>
        </font>
        </b>
        <font face="Tahoma">
        - You say hail Keeper Bile.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Tahoma" size="2">Keeper
        Bile bows before you as a gesture of kindness and respect. Greetings. I
        am Bile, Keeper of the Apprentice ranks. My knowledge is that of the
        first circles of necromany. I was once a great necromancer, but now I
        have a greater calling to protect the words of Kotiz. I also conduct
        many tests to insure the spells are deciphered correctly. I am in need
        of an apprentice to <font color="#FFFFFF">[collect components]</font>.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Tahoma" size="2">You
        say, ‘I will collect components’</font></p>
        <b>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        </b>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Tahoma" size="2">Keeper
        Bile takes out a tatterd scroll and looks upon it’s words. Hmm. Yes. I
        will need the following; One Large Scorpion Pincer, One Sabertooth Cub
        Canine and Two Brittle Skulls. Bring these to me and I shall pay you and
        if I also have an overscribed spell, I shall give you that also.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Tahoma" size="2">Keeper
        Bile is found near the Arena area in West Cabilis. He sells the level 1
        necro spells.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Tahoma" size="2">The
        Large Scorpion Pincer can be obtained as a pretty common drop from Large
        Scorpions in the Field of Bone. They are No Drop and the Large Scorpions
        are level 4-5. The Sabertooth Cub Canine appears to be a common drop of
        the Sabertooth Cubs in the Lake of Ill Omen (they are around level 3-4).
        And lastly, the Brittle Skulls are in fact the Brittle Iksar Skulls
        dropped by Skeletons of varrying variety found in many zones. The
        easiest place to aquire these skulls is in the Lake of Ill Omen off
        Decaying Skeletons, who appear to be pretty easy to find there.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Tahoma" size="2">The
        reward for the quest is some silver (I got 12) and the Coldlight spell,
        which is good for practicing conjuration, but other than that, it’s
        worthless. It can however be sold for some extra cash =)</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><b><font face="Tahoma" color="#FFFFFF">Outcome:</font>
        </b>
        <font face="Tahoma"> Some silver and a level 1 spell</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <b>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font face="Tahoma" color="#AEC3DB">Master
        Xydoz</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Tahoma"><font color="#FFFFFF">Julak</font>
        </font>
        </b>
        <font face="Tahoma">
        - Master Xydoz says ‘What is it that you seek within the tower? Could
        it be that you are a new apprentice? If so you are required to don the <font color="#FFFFFF">[Apprentice
        Skullcap]</font>.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">You
        say, ‘what Apprentice Skullcap?’</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">Master
        Xydoz says ‘All new members of the Brood of Kotiz are required to don
        the <font color="#FFFFFF">[Apprentice Skullcap]</font>. To earn one, a
        new apprentice is required to fetch four brains for further experiments.
        Not just any four brains, but the brains of [Sarnak] hatchlings. Often,
        they have under developed brains which are useless to us.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">You
        say, ‘what Sarnak?’</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">Master
        Xydoz says ‘Sarnak?!! Do not speak loudly, that name. If you seek
        information on the Sarnak then read the tome of this tower. The tower
        librarian should be found within.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">Master
        Xydoz can be found in the Necro Guild Tower where the guildmaster is
        located. He’s on the second to the highest ledge in front of a rack of
        brains in jars.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">This
        is a pretty simple quest. You must find Sarnak Hatchlings in the Lake of
        Ill Omen. They are around level 3-4 and drop brains semi-often... I
        believe they are No Drop. If you get any Tapestries, save them. You’ll
        need one Ripped and one Torn Tapestry for the second rank skullcap, so
        it’ll save you the trouble if you just start saving them now.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><b><font face="Tahoma" color="#FFFFFF">Outcome:</font>
        </b>
        <font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">First Rank Skullcap, AC 2</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma" color="#FFFFFF">Second
        Rank Skullcap Quest</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">You
        say, ‘What Second Rank Skullcap?’</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">Master
        Xydoz says ‘Looking for the Second Rank Skullcap? Look no further, but
        you shall earn it. I seek a <font color="#FFFFFF">[Faded Tapestry]</font>.
        Now too, so do you.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">You
        say, ‘What Faded Tapestry?’</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">Master
        Xydoz says ‘I have heard reports of such thing found upon sarnak
        hatchlings. They must have scampered from the safety of their dwelling
        with their masters property. I would like to see this tapestry, but only
        when it has been mended. I need to find a necromancer who is <font color="#FFFFFF">[adept
        at tailoring]</font>.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">You
        say, ‘I am adept at tailoring.’</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">Master
        Xydoz says ‘If you are a member of the Brood and wish to assist, you
        may seek out this tapestry. Find the Torn and Ripped pieces and take
        them both to a sewing kit. Return with the Mended Tapestry and your
        First Rank Skullcap then I shall see that you are rewarded with coin and
        a Second Rank Skullcap.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font SIZE="2" face="Tahoma">After
        completing the First Rank Skullcap quest, Master Xydoz will mention the
        Second Rank Skullcap. If you took my advise above, you saved one Ripped
        and one Torn Tapestry from the Sarnak Hatchlings in the Lake of Ill Omen
        (they are around level 3-4 for anyone that might be reading this but
        hasn’t read the one about the first rank skullcap). Placing these two
        objects into a tailoring kit and combining them will yield a Mended
        Tapestry (NO DROP, so you, unfortunally, must put some practice points
        into tailoring... shouldn’t take much). Turn the Mended Tapestry and
        First Rank Skullcap into Master Xydoz for the Second Rank Skullcap!</font></p>
        <p><b><font face="Tahoma" color="#FFFFFF">Outcome:</font>
        </b>
        <font face="Tahoma">Second Rank Skullcap, AC 3</font></p>
        <b>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font face="Tahoma" color="#AEC3DB">Master
        Rixiz</font></p>
        </b>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Tahoma"><b><font color="#FFFFFF">Julak</font></b>
        - Master Rixiz says ‘You are on the grounds of the Brood of Kotiz. If
        you do not belong then leave at once. There shall be no <font color="#FFFFFF">[Third
        Rank Skullcap]</font> for you.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">You
        say, ‘what Third Rank Skullcap?’</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Master
        Rixiz says ‘I offer the Third Rank Aprrentice Skullcap to those who
        wear the Second. If that is you then you will do the <font color="#FFFFFF">[bidding
        of the tower]</font>.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">You
        say, ‘I will do the bidding of the tower’</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Master
        Rixiz says ‘Take this Glass Canopic. Within it you shall place a brain
        for me. The brain I seek is of a Sarnak Crypt Raider. Any shall do. The
        ones we seek should be near the Lake of Ill Omen. When you obtain the
        brain you must quickly put it into the Glass Canopic with <font color="#FFFFFF">[Embalming
        Fluid]</font>. When these are combined the canopic shall seal and if you
        return it to me with your Second Rank Skullcap then I shall hand you the
        next and final skullcap.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">You
        say, ‘what Embalming Fluid?’</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Master
        Rixiz says ‘Embalming Fluid is created through brewing, but do not
        drink it!! You can find the process of brewing on our grounds.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Master
        Rixiz is again found in the Necro Guild Tower, on the second floor,
        again, in front of a rack of brains in jars. Apparently you must do the
        first 2 skullcap quests before he will even respond to the &quot;I will
        do the bidding of the tower&quot; phrase. This sounds at lot easier than
        it really is, unfortunally. The Sarnak Crypt Raiders can be found in the
        Lake of Ill Omen, I assume. I’ve heard they are around level 6-8.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Embalming
        Fluid, as Master Rixiz mentions, is brewed, thus forcing you to take up
        brewing as well. I assume a low skill, like 5, will do. He also mentions
        that the process of brewing can be found on their grounds. Apon exitting
        the guild tower, turn left and cross the wooden plank to the other side.
        Go in the door immediately on the other side and go up the stairs. There
        you will find the Mortician. He sells the recipe for Embalming Fluid for
        free. The ingrediants are: Rubbing Alcohol, 2 Bog Juice, and Bone
        Granite Powder. The Mortician sells the Rubbing Alcohol, and the Bog
        Juice can be brewed with a really low skill (Snake Scales, Water, and a
        Bottle. The Snake Scales can be found in the Swamp of No Hope from one
        of the venders near the city zone line. Make sure to buy water, not
        foraged, summoned, or that special type of water, I believe it’s
        called Broodwater or something like that, which is sold commonly in
        Cabilis). The Bone Granite Powder presents quite a problem however. Try
        asking the Mortician about it:</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">You
        say, ‘Where can I find Bone Granite Powder?’</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">a
        mortician says ‘It is as it sounds. Two of one and a pile of the
        others.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Hammered
        in heat until they are one.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Now,
        this leads me to believe that this stuff can be smithed, which most
        likely requires us necros to take up blacksmithing as a trade (although,
        I’m sure a low skill will do) as it is probably no drop. The bones are
        most likely Bone Chips (you’ll see why when I explain possibility
        number 2 below) and the Granite can be quested for in the form of a Pile
        of Granite Peebles. So, I assume this means that you will need two bone
        chips and one pile of granite peebles because the mortician mentions a
        &quot;pile&quot;. In East Cabilis, half way between the bank and the
        shaman guild (that big castle looking thing in front of the zone into
        the Field of Bone), there’s a small building. Just inside the door is
        a lizardman named The Toilmaster who mentions slaves crushing granite.
        Apparently monks can get him to talk a little more if they ask,
        &quot;What about the granite peebles?&quot; He says he will give you a
        pile of granite peebles for every two Broken Shackles you bring him.
        These can be found off of Escaped Frogloks in the Swamp of No Hope
        (around level 5, and are uncommon spawns). Aquire a pile of granite
        peebles and two bone chips and combine them in a forge (there’s on the
        East Cabilis, as well as a brewing barrel) for the Bone Granite Powder.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">A
        second possibility (assuming Bone Granite Powder is not no drop) would
        be to get a 20+ shaman to make the powder for you via Alchemy. Two bone
        chips and 3 piles of granite peebles I believe it was. However, this
        seems unlikely since the mortician speaks of heat and a hammer. That
        sounds more like a forge to me and I’m willing to bet the Bone Granite
        Powder is No Drop.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">However,
        assuming you can obtain the Bone Granite Powder, combine that, 2 Bog
        Juice, and Rubbing Alcohol in a brewing barrel for the Embalming Fluid.
        The Embalming Fluid and the brain from the Sarnak Crypt Raider into the
        jar Master Rixiz gave you, and the combined jar and your second rank
        skullcap to Master Rixiz for the third rank skullcap, which is most
        likely an AC of 4. This allows you to continue on to a (theoretically)
        must better skullcap which the guy in front of the pool of blood on the
        bottom floor of the necro guild tower speaks of.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">I
        will update this guide as I get more information.</font></p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <div>
          <div>
        <div>
          <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Tahoma"><b><font color="#FFFFFF">Julak</font></b>
        - I've been trying to do the 3rd apprentice skullcap quest in West
          Cabilis and have found out a few more things that you might find
          useful...</font>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">&nbsp;</font>
        </div>
            <div>
              <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font face="Tahoma">First,
              based on your suggestion, I tried 2 bone chips + pile of granite
              in a forge Result - &quot;those items do not combine in those
              quantities to produce anything&quot;</font>
            </div>
        <div>
          <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">I
          also tried 2 bone chips + pile of granite + 1 flask of
          water&nbsp;since a lot of blacksmithing requires water.&nbsp; Same
          result.</font>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">&nbsp;</font>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">After
          chatting with some additional NPC's in the city I did find out another
          useful <font color="#C0C0C0">tidbit.</font></font>
        </div>
            <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
            <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font color="#C0C0C0" size="2" face="Tahoma">There
            is a merchant named Jondin in a hut in West Cabilis who offers a
            quest for &quot;bone granite powder&quot;&nbsp; However, when you
            ask him about it, he gives a DIFFERENT formula than the one from the
            mortician.&nbsp; He says that it's made using alchemy and you need 3
            bone chips + the pile of granite.&nbsp; I'm not sure if this powder
            is the same as what you need for the embalming fluid and
            unfortunately I don't know anyone with alchemy, so I haven't been
            able to try it out.&nbsp;</font>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font color="#C0C0C0" size="2" face="Tahoma">&nbsp;</font>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font color="#C0C0C0" size="2" face="Tahoma">Also,
            getting the pile of granite is a real pain... You have to kill
            uncommon/rare spawn escaped frogloks in the Swamp of No Hope and it
            can take awhile to find them.&nbsp; Give 2 of the broken shackles
            they drop to the Toilmaster in East Cabilis and you get the pile of
            granite.</font>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font color="#C0C0C0" size="2" face="Tahoma">&nbsp;</font>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font color="#C0C0C0" size="2" face="Tahoma">I
            haven't found any of the NO DROP skeleton bones yet, or I would have
            tried 2 of those plus the granite in the forge.</font>
            <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;
            <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Tahoma"><b>Sethra</b></font><font face="Tahoma">
            - I tried the following to get the Bone Granite Powder and it
            worked: 2 bone chips, 1 pile of granite pebbles, 1 forging hammer
            (bought from a weaponsmith in the Warrior's Guild).</font>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin-left: 30; margin-right: 0; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</p>
        <p style="word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font face="Tahoma" color="#FFFFFF"><b>Outcome</b>:</font>
        <font face="Tahoma">?</font></p>
        </font>
      </div>
